[{"category":"section","location":"#NeuralLinearSolve.jl:-Neural-Network-Based-Linear-Solver-Selection","page":"Home","text":"NeuralLinearSolve.jl uses a pretrained convolutional neural network (CNN) to predict the fastest linear solver for a given sparse matrix. The sparse matrix is converted to a 64x64 spy plot image, which is fed into the CNN to predict the optimal solver from UMFPACK, KLU, and Pardiso.","title":"NeuralLinearSolve.jl: Neural Network-Based Linear Solver Selection"},{"category":"section","location":"#Installation","page":"Home","text":"To install NeuralLinearSolve.jl, use the Julia package manager:\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.add(\"NeuralLinearSolve\")","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","text":"using NeuralLinearSolve\nusing SparseArrays\n\nA = sprand(1000, 1000, 0.01)\n\n# Get the predicted fastest solver\nsolver = predict_solver(A)\n\n# Get the full probability distribution over solvers\nprobs = predict_solver_probs(A)","title":"Quick Start"},{"category":"section","location":"#API","page":"Home","text":"","title":"API"},{"category":"section","location":"#Contributing","page":"Home","text":"Please refer to the SciML ColPrac: Contributor's Guide on Collaborative Practices for Community Packages for guidance on PRs, issues, and other matters relating to contributing to SciML.\nSee the SciML Style Guide for common coding practices and other style decisions.\nThere are a few community forums:\nThe #diffeq-bridged and #sciml-bridged channels in the Julia Slack\nThe #diffeq-bridged and #sciml-bridged channels in the Julia Zulip\nOn the Julia Discourse forums\nSee also SciML Community page","title":"Contributing"},{"category":"section","location":"#Reproducibility","page":"Home","text":"<details><summary>The documentation of this SciML package was built using these direct dependencies,</summary>\n\nusing Pkg # hide\nPkg.status() # hide\n\n</details>\n\n<details><summary>and using this machine and Julia version.</summary>\n\nusing InteractiveUtils # hide\nversioninfo() # hide\n\n</details>\n\n<details><summary>A more complete overview of all dependencies and their versions is also provided.</summary>\n\nusing Pkg # hide\nPkg.status(; mode = PKGMODE_MANIFEST) # hide\n\n</details>\n\nusing TOML\nusing Markdown\nversion = TOML.parse(read(\"../../Project.toml\", String))[\"version\"]\nname = TOML.parse(read(\"../../Project.toml\", String))[\"name\"]\nlink_manifest = \"https://github.com/SciML/\" * name * \".jl/tree/gh-pages/v\" * version *\n                \"/assets/Manifest.toml\"\nlink_project = \"https://github.com/SciML/\" * name * \".jl/tree/gh-pages/v\" * version *\n               \"/assets/Project.toml\"\nMarkdown.parse(\"\"\"You can also download the\n[manifest]($link_manifest)\nfile and the\n[project]($link_project)\nfile.\n\"\"\")","title":"Reproducibility"},{"category":"function","location":"#NeuralLinearSolve.predict_solver","page":"Home","text":"Example\n\nusing SparseArrays, NeuralLinearSolve\n\nA = sprand(1000, 1000, 0.01)\nsolver = predict_solver(A)  # :KLU\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NeuralLinearSolve.predict_solver"},{"category":"function","location":"#NeuralLinearSolve.predict_solver_probs","page":"Home","text":"Example\n\nprobs = predict_solver_probs(A)\n# Dict(:UMFPACK => 0.05, :KLU => 0.91, :Pardiso => 0.04)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NeuralLinearSolve.predict_solver_probs"}]
